neering management. This page describes these groups and provides links to their sites.  As a UIC Engineering student, you also have the opportunity to join student organizations that are housed in the College’s other five departments. You can find them all here . Don’t forget that as a UIC student, you also can propose and create a student organization that you don’t see on this list.      student orgs           American Institute of Aeronautics and Astronautics  Members design and build remote-controlled aircraft, high-powered rockets, and quad-copters.             ASHRAE  ASHRAE promotes advancements in heating, ventilating, air conditioning, and refrigerating.             American Society of Mechanical Engineers  A professional organization for mechanical engineers that provides networking, employment opportunities, and more.             Engineering Design Team  Build robots for competition against other college teams from around the country.             Institute of Industrial and Systems Engineers  A professional organization that includes more than 15,000 industrial engineers worldwide.             Pi Tau Sigma  The national honor society for students of mechanical engineering.             Society of Automotive Engineers  Design, manufacture, test, and race two kinds of cars: a Formula-style car and an off-road mini Baja vehicle.               College-wide student organizations  Visit our college-wide student organizations page for information about other UIC College of Engineering student organizations, including interdisciplinary groups such as the National Association of Black Engineers, Society of Hispanic Professional Engineers, Society of Women Engineers, and Veterans in Engineering.   See all COE organizations            Undergraduate    Back to main content           Admitted Students    Admissions    Accreditation    Courses    ME Major    IE Major    EM Major    Minors    Internships and Jobs    Student Groups    Student Profiles    Student Resource